Ifeanyi Onuba, Abuja The Federal Government is engaging stakeholders in the manufacturing sector to boost the production of ethanol for making sanitisers. The move is expected to assist the government boost the supply of sanitisers and curtail the spread of the coronavirus pandemic in the country. Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Otunba Adeniyi Adebayo, said this on Thursday in Abuja at the weekly meeting of the Emergency Operation Centre of the Committee On Sustainable Production/Delivery of Essential Commodities During COVID-19. He said the collaboration would help to guarantee the availability of raw materials for the quick and mass production of sanitisers, a daily necessity in the fight against the pandemic. Copyright PUNCH.
